---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'April 22, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  lang="en"
  pathname="/en/privacy"
  title="Automata — Privacy Policy"
  description="What data we collect, why, who we share it with, and the rights you have over it."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <div class="section-index mb-8">
          <span>—</span>
          <span>Privacy</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="h-display mb-6">
          Privacy <em>policy</em>.
        </h1>
        <p class="t-lead mb-6 max-w-2xl">
          What data we touch, why, and what you can do about it.
        </p>
        <p class="t-caption t-mono">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section pt-0">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="max-w-3xl space-y-14">

        <div>
          <div class="label-upper mb-4">01 — Who we are</div>
          <h2 class="h-card mb-5">The operator of this site.</h2>
          <div class="t-body space-y-4">
            <p>
              This site is operated by <strong class="text-[color:var(--color-ink)] font-medium">AUTOMATA AI LLC</strong>,
              a limited liability company registered in the state of Kansas, United States. We are the
              <em>data controller</em> for the personal data described in this document.
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
              <li>Address: 17418 Jessica St, Gardner, Kansas 66030, USA</li>
              <li>EIN: 33-3383598</li>
              <li>Privacy contact: <a href="mailto:legal@beautomata.com" class="underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">legal@beautomata.com</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="hr-subtle" />

        <div>
          <div class="label-upper mb-4">02 — What we collect</div>
          <h2 class="h-card mb-5">The minimum to reply and keep the site alive.</h2>
          <div class="t-body space-y-4">
            <p>
              <strong class="text-[color:var(--color-ink)] font-medium">When you email us.</strong>
              If you contact us (for example at <span class="t-mono">hello@beautomata.com</span>) we receive
              your email address, the name shown by your mail client, and the content of your message.
            </p>
            <p>
              <strong class="text-[color:var(--color-ink)] font-medium">Technical logs.</strong>
              Our hosting provider, <span class="t-mono">Vercel</span>, temporarily logs IP addresses,
              browser type and requested URLs to protect the site from abuse and keep it running. We do not
              use these to build marketing profiles.
            </p>
            <p>
              <strong class="text-[color:var(--color-ink)] font-medium">No analytics.</strong>
              We do not run Google Analytics, Meta Pixel or similar tools. If that changes, we will say so
              here with a dated update before switching anything on.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="hr-subtle" />

        <div>
          <div class="label-upper mb-4">03 — Why we use it</div>
          <h2 class="h-card mb-5">Reply, operate, comply.</h2>
          <div class="t-body space-y-4">
            <p>We use the data above only to:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
              <li>Respond to your inquiry and, where relevant, send you a technical proposal.</li>
              <li>Keep the site secure and available.</li>
              <li>Meet applicable legal, accounting and tax obligations.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              Where GDPR (EU/EEA/UK) applies, our legal basis is <em>legitimate interest</em> (replying to
              an inquiry you started) or, where relevant, the <em>consent</em> you give by writing to us.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="hr-subtle" />

        <div>
          <div class="label-upper mb-4">04 — Who we share it with</div>
          <h2 class="h-card mb-5">One hosting provider. That's it.</h2>
          <div class="t-body space-y-4">
            <p>
              We do not sell or rent personal data. We share it only with providers we need to operate the
              site, under contract, always acting as <em>data processors</em>:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
              <li>
                <strong class="text-[color:var(--color-ink)] font-medium">Vercel Inc.</strong> (USA) —
                hosting, CDN and site-level technical logs.
              </li>
              <li>
                The <strong class="text-[color:var(--color-ink)] font-medium">email provider</strong> that
                runs our <span class="t-mono">@beautomata.com</span> mailboxes, when you contact us directly.
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              We may also disclose data when required to do so by a binding legal request from a competent
              authority.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="hr-subtle" />

        <div>
          <div class="label-upper mb-4">05 — International transfers</div>
          <h2 class="h-card mb-5">We operate from the United States.</h2>
          <div class="t-body space-y-4">
            <p>
              Because we are established in the United States, any data you send us travels to and is stored
              in the US. If you write from the European Economic Area or the United Kingdom, that
              international transfer is carried out under the European Commission's
              <em>Standard Contractual Clauses</em> or equivalent mechanisms recognized by applicable law.
            </p>
            <p>
              For Latin American residents (Brazil, Mexico, Colombia, Argentina, Chile, Peru, Uruguay, Ecuador
              and other countries with data-protection laws), international transfers to the United States
              rely on the mechanisms contemplated by each jurisdiction — primarily contractual clauses, the
              data subject's consent, or the equivalent standards recognized by the competent national
              authority (ANPD in Brazil, INAI in Mexico, SIC in Colombia, AAIP in Argentina, among others).
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="hr-subtle" />

        <div>
          <div class="label-upper mb-4">06 — How long we keep it</div>
          <h2 class="h-card mb-5">What the conversation and the law require — nothing more.</h2>
          <div class="t-body space-y-4">
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
              <li>
                <strong class="text-[color:var(--color-ink)] font-medium">Email inquiries</strong> — up to
                24 months after the last exchange, unless there is an active business relationship.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-[color:var(--color-ink)] font-medium">Vercel technical logs</strong> —
                per Vercel's retention policy (typically days to weeks).
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-[color:var(--color-ink)] font-medium">Contractual, accounting and tax
                records</strong> — for the periods required by applicable law.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="hr-subtle" />

        <div>
          <div class="label-upper mb-4">07 — Your rights</div>
          <h2 class="h-card mb-5">Access, correction, deletion, objection.</h2>
          <div class="t-body space-y-4">
            <p>
              Depending on where you live, you may exercise some or all of the following rights — under
              <em>GDPR</em> (EU/EEA/UK), <em>CCPA/CPRA</em> (California), <em>LGPD</em> (Brazil),
              <em>LFPDPPP</em> (Mexico), <em>Law 1581/2012</em> (Colombia), <em>Law 25.326</em> (Argentina),
              <em>Law 19.628</em> (Chile), <em>Law 29733</em> (Peru), and other applicable national privacy
              laws:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
              <li>Access the personal data we hold about you.</li>
              <li>Have inaccurate data corrected.</li>
              <li>Request its deletion.</li>
              <li>Object to, or restrict, processing.</li>
              <li>Request data portability.</li>
              <li>Withdraw consent when consent is the legal basis.</li>
              <li>Lodge a complaint with your supervisory authority (AEPD in Spain, ANPD in Brazil, INAI in Mexico, SIC in Colombia, AAIP in Argentina, among others).</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              To exercise any of these, email us at
              <a href="mailto:legal@beautomata.com" class="underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">legal@beautomata.com</a>,
              stating the applicable law and the right you want to exercise. We reply within 30 days at most,
              regardless of your jurisdiction.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="hr-subtle" />

        <div>
          <div class="label-upper mb-4">08 — Cookies</div>
          <h2 class="h-card mb-5">We do not use non-essential cookies.</h2>
          <div class="t-body space-y-4">
            <p>
              This site sets no analytics, advertising or tracking cookies. Our hosting provider may set
              strictly technical cookies for security and load balancing — these are not used to profile you.
              If we add analytics in the future, we will say so here and enable a matching consent flow.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="hr-subtle" />

        <div>
          <div class="label-upper mb-4">09 — Minors</div>
          <h2 class="h-card mb-5">This site is not directed at children under 16.</h2>
          <div class="t-body space-y-4">
            <p>
              We do not knowingly collect data from minors. If you believe a minor has sent us personal data,
              email us and we will delete it.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="hr-subtle" />

        <div>
          <div class="label-upper mb-4">10 — Changes</div>
          <h2 class="h-card mb-5">If it changes, you'll see it dated here.</h2>
          <div class="t-body space-y-4">
            <p>
              We may update this policy to reflect legal, technical or scope changes. Material changes will
              be reflected in the <em>Last updated</em> date at the top of this document.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="hr-subtle" />

        <div>
          <div class="label-upper mb-4">11 — Contact</div>
          <h2 class="h-card mb-5">One inbox, one person who answers.</h2>
          <div class="t-body space-y-4">
            <p>
              Any questions about this policy or how we handle your data — email us at
              <a href="mailto:legal@beautomata.com" class="underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">legal@beautomata.com</a>.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
